column1: Much less aquatic plant growth than previous years- but that could be because it is still early in the year and is still growing.
Light rainthe night before- but only enough to get the ground wet- nothing very significant.

Partly to mostly cloudy- 10 mph winds

Cloudy; 10-15 mph winds; 2 warm weeks before test date (70s and up to 80 degrees); not much rain; during cold front moving through

Cloudy/Rainy- drizzling off and on all day; colder than average temperatures; calm

Sunny- low 70's Fahrenheit- lots of rain previous 2 weeks-

column1: average to below average aquatic plant levels

Sunny and clear- 75 to 80 degrees Fahrenheit- sa 3 loons- lots of plant life near shore

Mostly sunny- cool (60s)- just recieved 4-5" of rain on Thursday- very windy conditions past 3-4 days (30-45 mph winds)
Sunny- warm for previous day or two including today (75-80 degrees)- no loons
1st measurement of the year. Secchi much lower than expected; calm- partly cloudy
Average temps; just recieved 4-6 inches of rain the previous week; sunny; satellite day
Very hot and humid the previous 2 days; today is windy and sunny; saw loons; much aquatic plant growth
Very hot and humid; cloudy and hazy; saw 2 loons; lots of plant growth once again
Hot; saw 2 loons; partly cloudy and hazy
Saw 2 loons; average temps; sunny day
Only saw one loon; warm - low 80's; not much rain past few weeks
Cold - froze the past few nights; did not see any loons; sunny
Sunny; cold all previous week and today; no loons once again
Warm all previous week including today; sunny
Cool; freezing at night (mid-20's); cloudy and scattered showers today
Mostly cloudy- cool; slight wind; saw two adult loons- no offspring
Cloudy and cool; lots of rain previous week and this morning; saw two loons in the distance
Sunny- warm and dry; breezy; didn't see any loons
Cloudy; light drizzle - right after heavy rainfall earlier in the day; heavy rain for two days prior; no loons

Mostly cloudy; warm and humid past few days with scattered showers today; no loons
Partly cloudy; lots of aquatic plants; heard loons; lots of small sunfish/catfish
Sunny; cool to average temps; no loons; very clear and pristine water quality; windy
Sunny and warm; very calm; saw two loons
Partly cloudy; seasonable temps; did not see any loons; windy
Mostly sunny; no wind; beautiful evening; trees in full color
Overcast; no wind; about 2-3" of rain previous week; no leaves on trees; saw one baby loon by itself
Overcast and windy; lots of rain past few weeks; no loons
Sunny; warm all week - mid 50s; windy
Clear and cool- somewhat windy- no loons- water level is higher than last year
Mostly sunny with average temps- saw two adult loons- lots of very small algae floating suspended throughout water
Sunny- warm and humid- no loons
Cold- rainy- overcast and windy- very cold weekend for July- no loons
Cloudy- saw two adult loons and baby loon- very calm- average temps
Average temps- sunny with a slight breeze- no loons- lots of aquatic vegetation

Sunny- hot and humid with a cold front moving through- windy
Mild day- sunny and calm- saw loons- very clear and beautiful water
Very clear water- mild day- sunny- beautiful water and beautiful fall day
Mostly sunny and calm- dirty looking water

Mostly calm- mostly sunny- saw loon- beautiful fall day- below average temps
Very warm- mostly sunny and calm- close to peak color- very colorful- no loons

Average temps; sunny with a slight breeze; not totally clear water; no loons; lily pads just beginning to form

Partly cloudy and windy; lots of seaweed chunks floating around
Mostly sunny; today and previous week has been hot and humid; saw family of loons; slight breeze

mid-40s temps; cloudy; slight breeze; saw 2 loons; water level very high
Sunny and calm; mid 70s; no loons; lots of suspended particles in water; saw bluegills- crappies and rock bass along shoreline
Partly sunny; light winds; saw 2 loons; water level very high; fairly murky water
Partly sunny; averafe temps; previous 2 weeks were very hot and humid; saw 2 loons

Sunny and calm; average temps; no loons; beautiful fall day
Overcast; 5-10 mph winds; average temps; no loons

Calm and overcast; a little foggy out
15-20 mph winds; cool; 3+ inches of rain past 3 days; water level very high; no loons sighted
Breezy; warm and humid and has been hot and humid for a few weeks prior to today; saw 2 loons
Calm and cloudy; very slight drizzle; saw one loon

Sunny and calm; checked two days in a row to see if clear and sunny skies today made a difference versus yesterday's conditions; yesterday's rain must've muddied the water up
Filtered sunshine; very warm and humid all week including today; no rain for a few weeks prior; no loons

Humid- sunny and warm; saw 2 loons

Extremely high water; saw 2 loons; mostly sunny with thin clouds
Very high water; saw 2 loons; mostly sunny; lots of floating debris/pollen on water and in the water
Very high water; saw a loon; cloudy and overcast; very wet and rainy spring/early summer
High water but 2-4" lower than spring; saw 1 loon; lots of aquatic vegetation/lily pads; sunny and calm
Saw 1 loon; very clear and beautiful water; sunny day; lots of rain the previous week
No loons; sunny; very rainy fall
Cold and wet fall; very cold this week; ice forming along edge of lake
Very high water; calm- sunny 50 degrees- clear top layer of water - surface to 3-4'- then got very murky below that level; saw one loon
Very high water; slight breeze; 60-65 degrees; sunny; saw loon
Highest water level I've ever seen on Lawrence Lake; mostly sunny; 85-90 degrees all week; saw one loon; lots of particulates in water; very dark water

Even higher water level than in July; 7" of rain last week - 1.5" this morning; calm and cloudy; no loons; mid-70 degrees- brown/red water Even higher water level than in July; 7" of rain last week - 1.5" this morning; calm and cloudy; no loons; mid-70 degrees- brown/red water; water and lake area smelled horrible
Still extremely high water; still smells funny; calm and sunny; 70 degrees; no loons; very murky water
very high water; no smell - smell is gone from lake area; sunny; mid-60 degrees; breezy; saw loon; lots of stuff floating in water
No loons; saw one eagle; no floating vegetation; minimal suspended particles; still looked dirty and murky; unseasonably warm - mid 60 degrees - sunny and calm
